Global Oncology Information Systems Market - Industry Overview

The global oncology information systems market is expanding rapidly, propelled by increasing cancer rates, advancements in technology, and a growing need for integrated solutions that enhance clinical and operational efficiency in oncology care. According to the National Cancer Institute (NCI), cancer remains a leading cause of death worldwide, with nearly 20 million new cases and 9.7 million cancer-related deaths reported in 2022. OIS encompasses a range of software tools designed to manage various aspects of cancer treatment, including electronic health records (EHRs), radiation therapy planning, and chemotherapy management. The market’s growth is fueled by rising cancer incidences and the demand for personalized treatment approaches that require advanced data management and analysis.

